HEADWORD: Peruse
<hw>Pe*ruse"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Perused</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Perusing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Pref. <ets>per-</ets> +
<ets>use</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To observe; to examine with
care.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Myself I then <qex>perused</qex>, and limb by limb⟦br⟧
Surveyed.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To read through; to read carefully.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peruser</ent>⟦br⟧
